user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following dir_reader code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 8.13.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 is A pointer should point to a const-qualified type whenever possible.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of dir_reader.
```c
static ssize_t
dir_reader (void *cls, uint64_t pos, char *buf, size_t max)
{
  DIR *dir = cls;
  struct dirent *e;
  int res;

  if (max < 512)
    return 0;
  (void) pos; /* 'pos' is ignored as function return next one single entry per call. */
  do
  {
    e = readdir (dir);
    if (e == NULL)
      return MHD_CONTENT_READER_END_OF_STREAM;
  } while (e->d_name[0] == '.');
  res = snprintf (buf, max,
                  "<a href=\"/%s\">%s</a><br>",
                  e->d_name,
                  e->d_name);
  if (0 >= res)
    return MHD_CONTENT_READER_END_WITH_ERROR;
  if (max < (size_t) res)
    return MHD_CONTENT_READER_END_WITH_ERROR;
  return (ssize_t) res;
}
```
</target_code>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
