<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The local pointer 'e' is declared as 'struct dirent *e' but is only used for read-only access (assigned from readdir(dir) and only used to inspect e->d_name). Per MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 it should be declared const, e.g. 'const struct dirent *e;', so the current declaration violates the rule.
</scenario>
